<! Cantina Siemens [2013] --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
					<section id="portfolio" class="projects_even">

					<div id="cantina_siemens">
							<header>
								<h2>Cantina Siemens [2013]</h2>
							</header>
							<div id="text_format">
								<ul>
									<li><strong>The Beginning</strong></li>
								</ul>
								<p>Cantina Siemens was initially seen with a simply entry door to the Android world, an entertainment to get a general overview over mobile applications programming. 
									Nevertheless it seem obvious that if it was to create something, it should be to create something new and useful above all.</p>
								<p>That's when things started to get serious: the project seemed interesting, especially when thinking of people actually using the application on a day-to-day basis.</p>
								<p>Before entering the details of this application however, a simple explanation on what it is all about is a must:</p>
								<ul><ul>
									<li>&#9658 Cantina Siemens was the canteen of my workplace, at Amadora-Lisbon, that serves daily meals both to the employees of <a class="link" href="http://www.siemens.com/entry/pt/pt/">Siemens</a>, <a href="http://www.nokiasiemensnetworks.com/" class="link">Nokia Siemens Networks</a>, and <a class="link" href="http://www.coriant.com/">Coriant</a>.</li><br>
									<li>&#9658 This canteen has different daily menus, whose contents are weekly updated on a proper website, thus allowing people to access the menus for the week.</li><br>
									<li>&#9658 The idea was to bring this access to the mobile world, without having to open a browser, writing the link, and reading the contents in an all messed up format.</li><br>
									<li>&#9658 <strong>The idea was to simplify!</strong></li><br>
								</ul></ul>
								<p>
									Before providing more details, it is important to state that the knowledge necessary to develop this App was obtained predominantly from Youtube videos, were I underline the contribution of Bucky Roberts <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/thenewboston" class="link">(TheNewBoston Youtube Channel)</a>  as well as from google searches, and that this was a 1st time experience.
								</p>
								<ul>
								<br>
								<li><strong>The Application</strong></li>
								</ul>
								<p>The application itself is rather simple, consisting on only 3 different views.</p>
								<ul>
								<ul>
									<li>&#9658 The Loading Screen</li>
									<li>&#9658 The Menu;</li>
									<li>&#9658 The Plate Listing (on both Portuguese and English).</li>
								</ul>
								</ul>
								<p>These views are found on the picture below:</p>
								<p style="text-align:centre;">
									<a href="images/cantina.png" data-lightbox="image-1">
										<img src="images/cantina.png" width="600"/>
									</a>
								</p>
								
								<p>As of the application's operation is as follows:</p>
								<ul>
								<ul>
									<li>&#9658 As the App is launched, if there is a network connection available the plates data is loaded into a String array, during which the loading screen is shown, otherwise, if there is no internet access, the user is prompted to check the network connections;</li><br>
									<li>&#9658 Then, the menu is loaded, where the user can launch the plate listing window in Portuguese or in English, or refresh the list, get some info on the application or exit it;</li><br>
									<li>&#9658 The last view contains the plates themselves and is divided in smaller windows, each for the corresponding day of the week. Here the user can swipe between days of the week. Additionally it can click on the plates and directly google about it, to get extra information.</li><br>
								</ul>
								</ul>
								<p>
									This application is currently publicly available for Android platform, where it can be found and downloaded from Google Play, for free.
								If you want to try it out, just download it by clicking on the image below.
