							<div id="text_format">
								<b>The name:</b> Luis Filipe Dias.<br><br>	
								<b>The degree:</b> Master in Electronics and Telecommunications, by the <b>University of Aveiro</b>.<br><br>	
								<b>The current whereabouts:</b> DTV Research in Lisbon, working as an <b>Embedded Systems Engineer</b>.<br><br>			
								<b>The main</b> professional interests:<br><br>		
								<ul >
									<li><b>&#9658 Radio-Frequency Electronics:</b> Antennas and Energy Harvesting Systems, since my thesis consisted on the study and development of efficient Energy Harvesting Circuits for generation of <b>no-cost illumination</b> (you can find more information here).</li><br>	
									<li><b>&#9658 Hardware Engineering:</b> 1.5 years working as a <b>Hardware Engineer</b> (Nokia Siemens Networks/Coriant), with cutting edge-hardware for fiber optics, sharpened my interest on this area of technology. Here are some things I learned:</li>
										<ul>
							       		<li>&#9642 To integrate a multidisciplinary team, responsible for the firmware integration of long-haul optical equipments;</li>
                						<li>&#9642 To execute and analyze hardware validation tests (surge testing, EMC, temperature tests, worst-case power consumption and others);</li>
                						<li>&#9642 To handle testing, measurement and characterization equipments for optical and high-frequency electrical interfaces (Optical Traffic Analyzers/Generators, High-Frequency Oscilloscopes, Variable Optical Attenuators, etc.);</li>
                						<li>&#9642 To comprehend and apply distinct standards/protocols, both internal and internationally regulated (ANSI, ITU-T, IEEE, ETSI,...)</li>
      								</ul>
									<li><b>&#9658 Embedded Systems Engineering:</b> my latest challenge, is about bridging between the hardware and the low level drivers, and then up the stack into the higher levels of the application. It has been a challenging but really worthwhile learning experience. Some of the things I do:</li>
										<ul>
											<li>&#9642 C - a lot!</li>
											<li>&#9642 Develop & debug embedded software for different chip-sets, architectures and hardware sets;</li>
											<li>&#9642 Work at different levels of the SW stack (from the device-drivers to the application);</li>
											<li>&#9642 Comprehend and modify build-systems (cmake, kbuild, ...);</li>
											<li>&#9642 Debug problems on the HW layer;</li>
											<li>&#9642 Prepare setups for SW validation tests;</li>
											<li>&#9642 Understand and enforce technical specifications;</li>
										</ul>
								</ul>
								Other non-related personal interests involve travelling, gastronomy, cinema, mountain biking, squash or table tennis.<br>
								If you wish to <b>contact me</b>, keep scrolling...<br>
